<body>
    <div class="container">
        <h1>Crispy Fried Chicken Recipe</h1>
        <img src="https://www.allrecipes.com/thmb/q-IfK20zxeyp1DgKWhrVp6CQ43w=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/AR-89268-triple-dipped-fried-chicken-beauty-4x3-3961ac838ddd41958e7cb9f49376cd68.jpg" alt="Crispy Fried Chicken">
        
        <div class="section">
            <h2>Ingredients</h2>
            <ul>
                <li>4 chicken drumsticks and 4 thighs (bone-in, skin-on)</li>
                <li>2 cups buttermilk</li>
                <li>2 cups all-purpose flour</li>
                <li>1 tbsp paprika</li>
                <li>1 tsp garlic powder</li>
                <li>1 tsp onion powder</li>
                <li>1 tsp salt</li>
                <li>1/2 tsp black pepper</li>
                <li>Vegetable oil (for frying)</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="section">
            <h2>Instructions</h2>
            <ol>
                <li>Marinate the chicken in buttermilk for at least 2 hours (or overnight) in the fridge.</li>
                <li>In a bowl, mix flour, paprika, garlic powder, onion powder, salt, and pepper.</li>
                <li>Remove chicken from buttermilk, letting excess drip off, then coat each piece in the flour mixture.</li>
                <li>Heat 2 inches of vegetable oil in a deep skillet or Dutch oven to 350째F (175째C).</li>
                <li>Fry the chicken in batches, 10-12 minutes per side, until golden brown and internal temp reaches 165째F (74째C).</li>
                <li>Drain on paper towels and serve hot!</li>
            </ol>
        </div>

        <div class="section">
            <h2>Tips</h2>
            <p>For extra crunch, double-dip the chicken: buttermilk, flour, buttermilk, flour again.</p>
            <p>Serve with mashed potatoes, coleslaw, or your favorite hot sauce.</p>
        </div>
    </div>
